e Jewish community, disparaged women, mocked gays, and generally despaired of modern life and contemporary culture. As the first study of Richler’s entire corpus, this book considers these issues in the context of a long career – one as consistent as it was varied – in which an ideological discourse often, but not always, evolved. Turning away from impressions, assumptions, and generalizations, many informed by Richler’s non-fiction and on-record comments, Mauer focuses instead on the substance of the novels themselves, finding there a restless search for lasting moral value.Mordecai Richler’s Imperfect Search for Moral Values explores the construction of literary texts that have made Richler one of the most intriguing and successful modern writers, as well as an essential voice in Canadian and Jewish literature in the second half of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEthics in literature. 0aRichler, Mordecai,-1931-2001-Criticism and interpretation. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Canadian.2bisacsh  aAmerican.  aAnti-Semitism.  aBronfmans.  aByronic.  aCanada.  aForster.  aFranklin Expedition.  aFrench.  aHolocaust.  aInuit.  aIsrael.  aJewish.  aKlein.  aLondon.  aMain.  aMontreal.  aOrwell.  aQuebec.  aSpain.  adementia.  agolem.  aliberal.  amessianism.  asatire.  asupererogation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022801317440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228013174423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228013174/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022